<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-321-776  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 321 776.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Database Systems  March 1990 v15 n1 p40(27).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>View updates in relational databases with an independent scheme.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Langerak, Rom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Database views are mappings that provide the user or applicationwith an appropriate way of looking at data.andP;  Updates specified ona view must be translated to the underlying database.andP;  Thetranslation problem for a relational model with indexed nulls inthe base model is explored.andP;  The class of views studied consistsof total projections of the representative instance, considered tobe the correct representation of all data in the database.andP;  Onlyindependent database schemes, in which global consistency isimplied by local consistency, are considered.andP;  View updates can beinsertions, deletions, or modifications of a single view tuple.andO;The constant complement method is shown to be too restrictive forapplication in such instances.andP;  Important structural properties ofextension joins are derived, leading to the presentation ofminimal algorithms for translating a single view-tuple update.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalData Base Management SystemsAlgorithmsInformation ProcessingRelational Data Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>